Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell[TextData[{
 "PHGN 570: Computational Project 2\n",
 StyleBox["Fourier Transforms and Phase Retrieval",
  FontSize->24,
  FontWeight->"Regular"]
}], "Chapter",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7552740620598*^9, 3.755274072243856*^9}, {
  3.755274695714754*^9, 3.75527469712357*^9}, {3.756556999834882*^9, 
  3.756557006974069*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"48264375-2681-44fa-89ef-\
d9e6f107159b"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Project Summary", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.755274163607428*^9, 
  3.755274166357678*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"836bb4d4-c4d3-46fc-9bab-\
898348d03f11"],

Cell["\<\
This project is composed of two individual efforts
1) A study of numerical Fourier transforms
2) Single diffraction pattern phase retrieval

Ultimately the goal of this project is to provide students with some basic \
numerical functions that they can use for the rest of the semester, for \
students to understand the difference between a numerical Fourier transform, \
a DFT, and an FFT and to gain some insight into iterated phase retrieval.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7552741528068542`*^9, 3.75527415801682*^9}, {
  3.7552742810456867`*^9, 3.755274291135635*^9}, {3.755274408601207*^9, 
  3.755274418462164*^9}, {3.755274487639176*^9, 3.7552745068734083`*^9}, {
  3.755282155565679*^9, 3.75528222686957*^9}, {3.755282372829183*^9, 
  3.7552823868703613`*^9}, {3.755283771377837*^9, 3.7552837714499607`*^9}, {
  3.755286700300742*^9, 3.755286707074732*^9}, {3.7565570114275227`*^9, 
  3.7565571709449577`*^9}, {3.756584562287716*^9, 3.756584565372775*^9}, {
  3.756819360144539*^9, 3.7568194015215893`*^9}, {3.7569126325894957`*^9, 
  3.7569126329601097`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"749fed14-e253-4514-aaac-\
a82b678f4fdc"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Deliverable", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.755282425706918*^9, 
  3.7552824275818157`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"ba070f3c-e3c8-4db5-9e6e-\
446179b945df"],

Cell["\<\
The deliverable for this project is working code and documentation \
articulating the results. The results are two-fold:
1. Produce code that performs a numerical Fourier transform in 3 ways
\t1.1 Summation form of the numerical Fourier transform (AKA nonuniform \
discrete Fourier transform)
\t1.2 Normalized fast Fourier transform
\t1.3 2D Matrix multiplication form of the numerical Fourier transform

2. Single diffraction pattern iterated phase retrieval\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->CompressedData["
1:eJxTTMoPSmViYGCQAGIQ/Ydv5/+Fv147mszv41gEpE/9niIJoi3kInVAdImF
sjuIZtJfDqaN769KAtHeX8+D6WfsIlkg+tbJEwUgWs8irQxE3xf/OA1E9zDL
