Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 2:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (1) Unshifted function (2) shifted function (3) cross-correlation using \
FFTs to find shift to within one pixel (4) upsampled cross-correlation to \
find shift to within 1/100",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["", "th"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7e59cc92-e469-4c5d-9fd9-f5d333175241"],
 " of a pixel. In this case, the shifts were defined to be: +50.52 in the \
x-direction and -20.12 in the y-direction. The return from the function was: \
Shifts [x,y]: 50.52, -20.12."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7565855407741613`*^9, 3.75658560111932*^9}, {
   3.756821771333438*^9, 3.756821873969625*^9}, {3.756836780824992*^9, 
