  3.756928183170742*^9, {3.756928727199359*^9, 
   3.75692872738696*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"19d37925-86b0-40ed-84b3-\
de4a698177b0"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 3:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (1) Unshifted function (2) shifted function (3) cross-correlation using \
FFTs to find shift to within one pixel (4) upsampled cross-correlation to \
find shift to within 1/10",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["", "th"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "a47c5457-f787-4e9f-9224-2aad2a091460"],
 " of a pixel. In this case, the shifts were defined to be: +20.1 in the \
x-direction and -50.7 in the y-direction. The return from the function was: \
Shifts [x,y]: 20.1, -50.7."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7565855407741613`*^9, 3.75658560111932*^9}, {
   3.756821771333438*^9, 3.756821873969625*^9}, {3.756836780824992*^9, 
   3.756836799450777*^9}, {3.7569254997548113`*^9, 3.756925517798092*^9}, {
   3.7569256151405373`*^9, 3.756925720077992*^9}, {3.756928188483333*^9, 
   3.756928201717434*^9}, {3.756928284375544*^9, 3.756928285420719*^9}, {
   3.7569283321811857`*^9, 3.756928422312549*^9}, 3.756928564248393*^9, {
   3.7570034709551783`*^9, 3.757003471266116*^9}},
 FontWeight->"Regular",ExpressionUUID->"3b9bb9c9-95ca-48b3-a643-019428c43525"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Demonstrate:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n\nShow that your program can calculate a subpixel shift between two \
images. The images can be anything, but this works best with finitely \
supported structures. Therefore, unless you have a preference, calculate the \
subpixel shift between two numerically sampled Gaussian functions i.e., the \
two-dimensional extension of the one-dimensional example I gave above."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.756917921507002*^9, 3.7569180436225147`*^9}, {
   3.756919352579357*^9, 3.756919405139917*^9}, {3.756919440248527*^9, 
   3.7569194997364883`*^9}, {3.756919984022897*^9, 3.75691999019685*^9}, {
   3.7569200942705107`*^9, 3.756920095634413*^9}, 3.756921046080002*^9, {
   3.756957438465872*^9, 3.756957443103972*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.87, 0.94, 1],ExpressionUUID->"9818b456-8484-4ffa-a0b4-620a1d80304c"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Questions:\n",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\nThe matrix multiplication code you have written may be used to calculate \
two-dimensional Discrete Fourier transforms. In that case:\n\n1) Plot the \
real part of the matrix and discuss what the rows/columns of matrix actually \
are.\n\n2) What would be the result of this prescription if you did NOT \
conjugate one of the images?\n\n3) In light of question (2) above, could this \
routine still be used to find the relative shift between two shifted images?\n\
\n4) Will your code still work if the first function is not centered on the \
grid? What happens in that case?"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.756917921507002*^9, 3.7569180436225147`*^9}, {
   3.756919352579357*^9, 3.756919405139917*^9}, {3.756919440248527*^9, 
   3.7569194997364883`*^9}, {3.756919984022897*^9, 3.75691999019685*^9}, {
   3.7569200942705107`*^9, 3.756920095634413*^9}, {3.756920276891828*^9, 
   3.756920279240922*^9}, {3.756921067862537*^9, 3.756921073147283*^9}, {
   3.756921184010026*^9, 3.756921241461565*^9}, {3.756921288541091*^9, 
   3.7569212935790987`*^9}, {3.756921377536873*^9, 3.756921456953081*^9}, 
   3.75692156102009*^9, {3.756923061410646*^9, 3.7569230721711903`*^9}, {
   3.756957703654203*^9, 3.756957704272131*^9}, {3.756958156036243*^9, 
   3.756958180173229*^9}, {3.75700350815844*^9, 3.757003510828076*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.87, 0.94, 1],ExpressionUUID->"664032e1-2aa3-4c17-b4f3-ebdd0d7af691"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["PART II: Discrete 2D Fourier transform ",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["(",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  Background->RGBColor[1, 0.85, 0.85]],
 StyleBox["NO CODE",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0],
  Background->RGBColor[1, 0.85, 0.85]],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  Background->RGBColor[1, 0.85, 0.85]],
 StyleBox["!!",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0.5, 0],
  Background->RGBColor[1, 0.85, 0.85]],
 StyleBox[" ",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  Background->RGBColor[1, 0.85, 0.85]],
 StyleBox["JUST ANSWER THE QUESTIONS",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0],
  Background->RGBColor[1, 0.85, 0.85]],
 StyleBox[")",
  FontWeight->"Bold",
  Background->RGBColor[1, 0.85, 0.85]],
 "\nThe 2D Discrete Fourier transform is defined as: ",
 StyleBox["(wiki is a nice reference here: \
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discrete_Fourier_transform)",
  FontSize->9,
  FontWeight->"Regular"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7568366277052937`*^9, 3.756836643030362*^9}, 
   3.7568370914339542`*^9, 3.7568371276627893`*^9, {3.756920398520431*^9, 
   3.756920407575746*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"daa2432a-8680-42a6-8a67-\
d2cc7ef43938"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "\n\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{
    SubscriptBox[
     OverscriptBox["F", "~"], 
     RowBox[{"k", ",", " ", "l"}]], "=", 
    RowBox[{
     FractionBox["1", 
      SqrtBox[
       RowBox[{"M", "\[InvisibleComma]", "N"}]]], 
     SubsuperscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
      RowBox[{"m", "=", "1"}], "M"], 
     SubsuperscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
      RowBox[{"n", "=", "1"}], "N"], 
     SubscriptBox["f", 
      RowBox[{"n", ",", " ", "m"}]], 
     SuperscriptBox["\[ExponentialE]", 
      RowBox[{
       RowBox[{"-", "2"}], "\[Pi]", " ", "\[ImaginaryI]", " ", 
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         RowBox[{"k", " ", 
          FractionBox["n", "N"]}], "+", 
         RowBox[{"l", " ", 
          FractionBox["m", "M"]}]}], ")"}]}]]}]}], TraditionalForm]],
  ExpressionUUID->"9b99335a-5311-4eb5-a076-8869641eecd7"],
 "\n\nthis form has advantages and disadvantages compared with the numerical \
Fourier transform algorithm. An example of a 2D discrete Fourier transform is \
shown below:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{
  3.756579838874003*^9, {3.7565804540118923`*^9, 3.7565804621545477`*^9}, {
