  3.7568217429225883`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"67542c98-26e0-453a-b55b-\
010494e74831"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Figure 3:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " 2D DFT. The left column shows the input amplitude, input phase, and a \
profile taken along the matching colored lines in the 2D images. The right \
column is the 2D discrete Fourier transform plotted in amplitude, phase, and \
profiles taken along the matching colored lines in the 2D images."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.7565855407741613`*^9, 3.75658560111932*^9}, {
   3.756821771333438*^9, 3.756821873969625*^9}, {3.756836780824992*^9, 
   3.756836799450777*^9}, 3.7569254997548113`*^9},
 FontWeight->"Regular",ExpressionUUID->"d3317254-160a-40aa-94ee-1a0bb9b37478"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Questions:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n\n1) What are the advantages of calculating the Fourier transform in this \
way?\n\n2) What are some disadvantages?\n\n3) Would power always be conserved \
(in a Parseval\[CloseCurlyQuote]s theorem manner) for this transform?\n\n4) \
What is the meaning of the checkerboard pattern in the Fourier phase image? \
Provide a brief discussion on what the phase is actually doing in this \
example."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.756588206413381*^9, 3.756588223583425*^9}, {
  3.756836597572315*^9, 3.756836599478894*^9}, {3.756836664642046*^9, 
  3.756836713615759*^9}, {3.756844880323799*^9, 3.7568448804811993`*^9}, {
  3.7569202556584272`*^9, 3.7569202577126637`*^9}, {3.756920288306466*^9, 
  3.75692029325235*^9}, {3.7569204179984426`*^9, 3.756920420809474*^9}},
 FontWeight->"Regular",
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.87, 0.94, 1],ExpressionUUID->"59d07db7-4c01-43a1-8c9c-2351dd405fbb"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["2. Iterated Phase Retrieval", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.755274445590074*^9, 3.7552744559729652`*^9}, {
  3.756557368938217*^9, 3.756557373555656*^9}, {3.756560675677437*^9, 
  3.756560675919579*^9}, {3.756580408821577*^9, 3.756580430387206*^9}, {
  3.756584551875819*^9, 
  3.7565845527677393`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3661e26e-161a-4bf0-b866-\
1b0abdc4cae1"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Following the discussion in Goodman 4th edition, Chapter 2, Section 2.7 \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Phase Retrieval from Fourier Magnitude\
\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] write an algorithm that retrieves a real-space image \
from the diffraction pattern amplitude named \
\[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]fourierMagnitude.txt\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] included \
in the assignment .zip folder (you can use Matlab\[CloseCurlyQuote]s csvread \
function to import the data). The Fourier magnitude is the square-root of the \
Fourier intensity. You will use your normalized FFT functions for this task. \
In the following discussion, the \[OpenCurlyQuote]support\[CloseCurlyQuote], \
S, is a square of value 1 (that you will make) that is 111 pixels in height \
and 111 pixels in width, centered on a grid of zeros with 512\[Times]512 \
pixels.\n\nThe Pseudo code for this algorithm is:\n\nBefore Main Loop:\na) \
Create a \[OpenCurlyQuote]guess\[CloseCurlyQuote] for the complex diffraction \
pattern:    ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{
     SuperscriptBox["G", "\[Prime]"], "=", 
     RowBox[{
      RowBox[{"F", " ", "."}], "*", " ", "exp", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{"1", 
        RowBox[{"i", "/", "2"}], " ", "*", 
        RowBox[{"(", 
         RowBox[{
          RowBox[{"rand", 
           RowBox[{"(", 
            RowBox[{"M", ",", "N"}], ")"}]}], "-", "0.5"}], ")"}]}], 
       ")"}]}]}], ";"}],
   FontWeight->"Bold"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "d6b554c3-27aa-47d6-b6cb-73e6972ec6e2"],
 "\nwhere \[OpenCurlyQuote]F\[CloseCurlyQuote] is the Fourier magnitude you \
downloaded and imported. We supply a random phase to help the algorithm to \
not get \[OpenCurlyQuote]stuck\[CloseCurlyQuote] in a local minimum.\n\nb) \
Create a \[OpenCurlyQuote]guess\[CloseCurlyQuote] for the reconstructed, \
real-space image: This is just the inverse Fourier transform (FFT) of    ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"g", "=", 
     SuperscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalF]", 
      RowBox[{"-", "1"}]]}], "\[InvisibleComma]", 
    RowBox[{"{", 
     SuperscriptBox["G", "\[Prime]"], "}"}]}],
   FontWeight->"Bold"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "6c0e9312-bf29-4a3a-8df6-2525d25deb0f"],
 "\n\nInside Main Loop:\n1) Calculate ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["g", "\[Prime]"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "7a66dc41-5efc-4d7e-95e3-0de8967fe058"],
 " by inverse Fourier transforming ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["G", "\[Prime]"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "b1bf8dfb-9978-4281-a53f-b62bf3796d36"],
 ":    ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox[
     StyleBox["g",
      FontWeight->"Bold"], "\[Prime]"], 
    StyleBox["=",
     FontWeight->"Bold"], 
    StyleBox[
     SuperscriptBox["\[ScriptCapitalF]", 
      RowBox[{"-", "1"}]],
     FontWeight->"Bold"]}], 
   StyleBox["\[InvisibleComma]",
    FontWeight->"Bold"], 
   StyleBox[
    RowBox[{"{", 
     SuperscriptBox["G", "\[Prime]"], "}"}],
    FontWeight->"Bold"]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ed19f9da-36a2-47b0-84e1-bfb802b974cf"],
 "\n\n2) Follow the formula for the hybrid input-output algorithm\n\n\t",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"g", "\[InvisibleComma]", 
    RowBox[{"=", 
     TagBox[GridBox[{
        {"\[Piecewise]", GridBox[{
           {
            SuperscriptBox["g", "\[Prime]"], 
            RowBox[{
             OverscriptBox["x", "\[RightVector]"], "\[Element]", "S"}]},
           {
            RowBox[{"g", "\[InvisibleComma]", 
             RowBox[{
              RowBox[{"-", "\[Beta]"}], " ", 
              SuperscriptBox["g", "\[Prime]"]}]}], 
            RowBox[{
             OverscriptBox["x", "\[RightVector]"], "\[NotElement]", " ", "S"}]}
          },
          AllowedDimensions->{2, Automatic},
          Editable->True,
          
          GridBoxAlignment->{
           "Columns" -> {{Left}}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, 
            "Rows" -> {{Baseline}}, "RowsIndexed" -> {}},
          
          GridBoxItemSize->{
           "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, 
            "Rows" -> {{1.}}, "RowsIndexed" -> {}},
          GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
              Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
               Offset[0.84]}, 
              Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, "Rows" -> {
              Offset[0.2], {
               Offset[0.4]}, 
              Offset[0.2]}, "RowsIndexed" -> {}},
          Selectable->True]}
       },
       GridBoxAlignment->{
        "Columns" -> {{Left}}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, "Rows" -> {{Baseline}},
          "RowsIndexed" -> {}},
       GridBoxItemSize->{
        "Columns" -> {{Automatic}}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, "Rows" -> {{1.}}, 
         "RowsIndexed" -> {}},
       GridBoxSpacings->{"Columns" -> {
           Offset[0.27999999999999997`], {
            Offset[0.35]}, 
           Offset[0.27999999999999997`]}, "ColumnsIndexed" -> {}, "Rows" -> {
           Offset[0.2], {
            Offset[0.4]}, 
           Offset[0.2]}, "RowsIndexed" -> {}}],
      "Piecewise",
      DeleteWithContents->True,
      Editable->False,
      SelectWithContents->True,
      Selectable->False]}]}],
   FontWeight->"Bold"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "edddd6cc-ac72-44b4-8c52-fac001829735"],
 "\n\twhere ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"0", "\[LessEqual]", "\[Beta]", "<", "1"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "628f5ca8-46f6-4814-82f9-c1eb394867ab"],
 ", and usually we set ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[Beta]", "=", "0.9"}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "fa16b4fd-2b3d-4534-89f8-9205c495f578"],
 "\n\n3) Then set ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"g", "=", 
    RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", "g", "\[RightBracketingBar]"}]}],
   FontWeight->"Bold"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "1ad5ceee-7e91-4b60-b648-6b3b0983c697"],
 ". This is \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]a priori\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \
information about the reconstruction. It simply says the object, ",
 Cell[BoxData["g"],
  FormatType->"StandardForm",ExpressionUUID->
  "d06ceab4-18e8-459e-87fe-41db2c8a8b41"],
 ", had constant phase.\n\n4) Fourier transform to frequency space ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{
    RowBox[{"G", "=", "\[ScriptCapitalF]"}], "\[InvisibleComma]", 
    RowBox[{"{", "g", "}"}]}],
   FontWeight->"Bold"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "967cd9b7-f98a-46b9-b835-c266e79ed542"],
 "\n\n5) Apply the \[OpenCurlyQuote]modulus constraint\[CloseCurlyQuote]: ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{
    SuperscriptBox["G", "\[Prime]"], "=", " ", 
    RowBox[{
     RowBox[{"F", " ", "."}], "*", " ", 
     RowBox[{"G", "/", 
      RowBox[{"(", 
       RowBox[{
        RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", "G", "\[RightBracketingBar]"}], "+", 
        RowBox[{"1", "e"}], "-", "10"}], ")"}]}]}]}],
   FontWeight->"Bold"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "ace2bbc3-63c9-47c1-a346-008da3b698cb"],
 " where the small number in the denominator is a regularization parameter to \
prevent numerical overflow.\n\n6) Calculate the error defined by\n\n",
 Cell[BoxData[
  StyleBox[
   RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalE]", "=", 
    SqrtBox[
     RowBox[{
      FractionBox["1", 
       RowBox[{"N", " ", "M"}]], 
      SubscriptBox["\[CapitalSigma]", 
       RowBox[{"i", "\[InvisibleComma]", "j"}]], 
      SuperscriptBox[
       RowBox[{"(", 
        RowBox[{
         SubscriptBox["F", 
          RowBox[{"i", "\[InvisibleComma]", "j"}]], " ", "-", " ", 
         RowBox[{"\[LeftBracketingBar]", 
          SubscriptBox["G", 
           RowBox[{"i", "\[InvisibleComma]", "j"}]], 
          "\[RightBracketingBar]"}]}], ")"}], "2"]}]]}],
   FontWeight->"Bold"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "f5b451aa-7249-4c0f-ba96-f0766a751c78"],
 "\n\nwhere the summation is taken over all pixels in the difference between \
the Fourier modulus, F, and the absolute value of the algorithm\
\[CloseCurlyQuote]s guess for the Fourier modulus ",
 Cell[BoxData["G"],ExpressionUUID->"54a995c3-e57a-4533-adc7-43a77f501452"],
 " (or ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  SuperscriptBox["G", "\[Prime]"]],ExpressionUUID->
  "64a7809e-80be-4709-b1b8-03aaa39ab404"],
 "). \n\nGO TO (1)\n\nIterate until the error drops below ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  RowBox[{"\[ScriptCapitalE]", "\[LessEqual]", 
   SuperscriptBox["10", 
    RowBox[{"-", "3"}]]}]],ExpressionUUID->
  "4a4e2c34-fa8d-44f0-be0c-90206fb7a576"]
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.756931060553832*^9, 3.756931068609294*^9}, {
   3.7569312538767147`*^9, 3.756931383128714*^9}, {3.7569314730503273`*^9, 
   3.756931493857732*^9}, {3.7569338421472178`*^9, 3.756933906371153*^9}, {
   3.756934001467473*^9, 3.7569340713051243`*^9}, {3.756934105798377*^9, 
   3.756934406798251*^9}, {3.7569527276808157`*^9, 3.756952846148985*^9}, {
   3.756952887242532*^9, 3.75695289965368*^9}, {3.756952931146409*^9, 
   3.756952954906773*^9}, {3.756953009848843*^9, 3.7569530245471973`*^9}, {
   3.756953064148149*^9, 3.7569531204003277`*^9}, {3.756953218591733*^9, 
   3.756953291884695*^9}, {3.7569539715479383`*^9, 3.756953971548311*^9}, {
   3.756954242192528*^9, 3.7569542473435802`*^9}, {3.756954468609682*^9, 
   3.756954511519779*^9}, {3.756954544520846*^9, 3.756954547426737*^9}, {
   3.756954634846794*^9, 3.756954663248045*^9}, {3.756954739876524*^9, 
   3.756954741346739*^9}, {3.756954794691779*^9, 3.756954798315065*^9}, {
   3.756954867391055*^9, 3.7569548786475773`*^9}, {3.756954974612934*^9, 
   3.756955005493648*^9}, {3.756955241692477*^9, 3.756955257280088*^9}, 
   3.7569554861194468`*^9, {3.756955644967164*^9, 3.756955677841297*^9}, {
   3.756955717176588*^9, 3.756955723476467*^9}, {3.7569564540872498`*^9, 
   3.756956484525091*^9}, {3.756957575422524*^9, 3.756957576667021*^9}, {
   3.75695820078876*^9, 3.756958276069543*^9}, {3.757003646418621*^9, 
   3.757003766077366*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"a64f574f-1d61-48bb-9141-\
58897c80c414"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Demonstrate:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n\nShow a plot of your final reconstructed amplitude."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.756917921507002*^9, 3.7569180436225147`*^9}, {
   3.756919352579357*^9, 3.756919405139917*^9}, {3.756919440248527*^9, 
   3.7569194997364883`*^9}, {3.756919984022897*^9, 3.75691999019685*^9}, {
   3.7569200942705107`*^9, 3.756920095634413*^9}, 3.756921046080002*^9, {
   3.756957081736829*^9, 3.756957098681595*^9}, {3.7569572658349943`*^9, 
   3.756957266388164*^9}, {3.756957448341988*^9, 3.756957449842572*^9}},
 Background->RGBColor[
  0.87, 0.94, 1],ExpressionUUID->"b3abc462-7548-4d3d-8ed8-3d71ef651963"],

Cell[TextData[{
 StyleBox["Questions:",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n\n1) Does it reconstruct the same way every time?\n\n2) In light of the \
fact that the exact dimensions of the support were given to you, describe how \
this algorithm could be used to encrypt information."
}], "Text",
